('DOT', 'DOTA', 13, 'A multiplayer online battle arena', '<i>Three paths,<br/>\r\nTwo Ancients,<br/>\r\nTen heroes,<br/>\r\nThe destiny lies in your hands.<br/> \r\nRemember, itâ€™s a team game.<br/><br/></i>\r\n\r\nNIT Calicut proudly presents<br/>\r\nDOTA!<br/><br/> \r\n\r\nDota combines the real-time strategy element of traditional top-down perspective, while also incorporating levelling and itemization functions of a role-playing video game. Players are pitted against each other as two distinct factions called the Sentinel and the Scourge. The Sentinel is a faction based at the southwest corner of the map, while the Scourge is a faction based at the northeast corner. Players assume the role of one of hundred and ten "heroes"&#8211; strategically powerful units with special abilities, who, through combat experience, may progress to a maximum level of twenty-five. The heroes&#39; methods of combat are heavily influenced by their primary property, which can be physical strength, agility, or intelligence. The basic setup of Dota places two strongholds containing critical structures called "Ancients" at opposing ends of a geographically balanced map. These bases are connected by three main paths (referred to as "lanes"), which are guarded by defensive towers and groups of weaker units commonly referred to as "creeps" periodically spawned, which traverse their lanes, attacking enemy units and structures upon sight. Players are split into two teams, each consisting of five players, to compete as the primary defenders for each Ancient.<br/>\r\n||sec||Rules and Regulations||ttl||<ul>\r\n<li>Registration Fees: Rs. 750/- per team (This is excluding Ragam registration and at least 1 member should have a Ragam registration.)</li>\r\n<li>Competition format: 5v5 Teams</li>\r\n<li>Match format: Single elimination i.e., Knockout (may be changed to Double Elimination if feasible)</li>\r\n<li>Match winner: The team who destroys the opponent&#39;s fortified Ancient first, or the team who&#39;s opponent surrenders by typing gg/ff/forfeit into the All-Chat.</li>\r\n<li>Finals will be &#39;Best of 3 games&#39; and all other rounds will be single game only.</li>\r\n<li>Drafting mode: -cm</li>\r\n<li>Item Restrictions: None</li>\r\n<li>Coin Toss: Winner</li><br/>\r\n<u>General Instructions:</u><br/><br/>\r\n<li>Teams must report to the venue at the time informed. If they cannot report within 10mins of allotted time, they will be disqualified. The time will be informed in the contact provided by the team at least 45 minutes in advance.</li>\r\n<li>The administrator&#39;s decision will be final in case of any dispute.</li>\r\n<li>Game will be hosted by Ragnarok using referees.</li>\r\n<li>Team members are not allowed to change seats once the DOTA map has started to load.</li>\r\n<li>At the end of the match, competitors must maintain the final screenshots and receive the confirmation from the admin.</li>\r\n<li>Backdooring is allowed. </li>\r\n<li>Sharing of items is allowed as long as the game permits.</li>\r\n<li>Control Sharing is allowed.</li>\r\n<li>Abuse & Exploitation:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Trees trapping: intentionally trapping enemies in trees is not allowed (except Furion&#39;s skill).</li>\r\n<li>Pause Abuse: From the point after hero selection process is completed, pausing without any valid reason is not allowed.</li>\r\n<li>Bug Exploitation: Exploitation of any known or newly discovered bug during the match will result in an immediate disqualification of the team. Excuses will not be entertained. Not knowing the bug is not an excuse; competitors are expected to know the current bugs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Definition of Bugs\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Anything abnormal which will give a competitor / team an unfair advantage.</li>\r\n<li>Anything which will cause interruption / fatal error to the game.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Penalties\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Warning: After a warning is given, the game goes on. If these warnings are accumulated by the team during the match, the team will be disqualified from the tournament.</li>\r\n<li>Game Loss: A &#39;Game loss&#39; given to a team means that the team will automatically lose the game, irrelevant of the actual match result.</li>\r\n<li>Disqualifications: A team disqualification will lead to the team being removed from the tournament. They will not be allowed to take part in the current event.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Any competitor found to have intentionally disconnected from the game will give that competitor&#39;s team a loss for that match.</li>\r\n<li>If any of the competitors are disconnected, the game can be paused by either the team mates or the referees and resumed after both teamsâ€™ approval.</li>\r\n<li>No random chats are allowed in all-chat during the game. Request for pause or save can be made by either captain at any point.</li>\r\n<li>Players are required to conduct themselves in a professional manner, showing sportsmanship and respect for everyone involved. Any flaming or insulting will result in team-disqualification.</li>\r\n<li>Team or player names may not be vulgar. While it is up to the adminsâ€™ discretion, as a guideline, avoid the following: profanity, hate-speech, drug use, or sexual references.</li>\r\n<li>Gaming accessories like mouse, keyboard, headset and mike are entertained at the userâ€™s risk.</li>\r\n</ul>||sec||Prize Money||ttl||First - INR 20000<br/>\r\nSecond - INR 5000<br/>', 'dota, dota 2, gaming, ', 'Sebin P S||@||9400630872||@||gaming||0||Jithin Thomas Paul||@||9496321073||@||gaming||0||||@||||@||gaming||0||', 'First - INR 20000<br/>\r\nSecond - INR 5000<br/>', '5||@||5', 0),
('DOV', 'DOTA 1v1', 13, 'A single player online battle arena', '<i>Do you think you have enough skills<br /> \r\nTo beat everyone head to head?<br />\r\nWell, letâ€™s see what you&#39;ve got.<br /><br />\r\n</i>\r\n||sec||Rules and Regulations||ttl||<ul>\r\n<li>Entry fee of INR 100 per head</li>\r\n<li>Gaming mode will be &#8211;apom and the starting gold will be 603 as in default mode.</li>\r\n<li>No bottle crow, soul ring or neutrals.</li>\r\n<li>Three predefined matchups will be given.</li>\r\n<li>Each player secretly votes on any 1 matchup, which will be banned.</li>\r\n<li>If both players vote on the same matchup, a coin flip determines which of the remaining 2 will be chosen.</li>\r\n<li>A coin flip will also determine the side chosen i.e. Sentinel or Scourge.</li>\r\n<li>The first player to get either 2 kills or 2 towers wins.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br/><br/>\r\nThe match format is as follows:<br/><br/>\r\nIt is a best of three formats, where each player exchanges the heroes chosen in the 1st match, with rules remaining the same. If the 1st two matches are tied, then we go for the tiebreaker match, which are the SF vs. SF only mid without any items or runes. In this 3rd match, either first blood or first tower kill decides the winner.||sec||Prize Money||ttl||First - INR 2000<br/>', 'DOTA, dota 1v1, gaming', 'Sebin P S||@||9400630872||@||gaming||0||Jithin Thomas Paul||@||9496321073||@||gaming||0||||@||||@||gaming||0||', 'First - INR 2000<br/>', '1||@||1', 0),
