('SWA', 'Swara Raaga', 9, 'The Kurukshetra of music!', '<img src="/2013/images/events/swaaragga_resized.jpg" alt="swaaragga.jpg"/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n<i>Ragam brings to you the chance of living the rhapsody that comes along with playing some awesome music with a desi twist. Brace yourself to lock horns with some of the best bands of South India and redefine music in your own style. So tune up your instruments and gear up to charm your audience with an enchanting spell.</i>||sec||Rules and Regulations||ttl||\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>One team per college</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Maximum of 20 members per team</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Time limit: 15 min + 3min set up time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Teams are permitted to perform in any regional language of their choice. </li><br>\r\n<li>Instruments used should be in clean patch with no distortion/modifiers.</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Participating teams should upload a video of any of their performance in YouTube and send its URL to     swararaaga@ragam.org.in on or before March 7th, along with the following details:<br/>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>College Name (and Band Name, if any)</li>\r\n<li>Name and Contact Info of the Team Leader</li>\r\n<li>List of Team members</li>\r\n</ul></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Finalists will be screened based on the video sent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Registration will be confirmed only after receiving the confirmation letter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is no On the Spot Registration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Members of the team need not necessarily be from the same college (but in this case, the colleges in  consideration wonâ€™t receive any points).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A team manager is requested to be present near the sound engineer 5 minutes before the performance of  the team so as to ensure proper sound levelling </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The same person cannot be a part of two participating teams</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Instruments other than drums (standard 5-piece drum kit) will not be provided</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All music should be played live on stage</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Points: (45, 32, 24)</li>\r\n</ul>||sec||Prize Money||ttl||First - INR 15000<br>\r\nSecond - INR 10000<br>\r\nThird - INR 5000', 'music, classical, ', 'Akhil Sanalkumar||@||9497426783||@||swararaaga||0||Nitheesh I S||@||9497269030||@||swararaaga||0||||@||||@||swararaaga||0||', 'First - INR 15000<br>\r\nSecond - INR 10000<br>\r\nThi', '-||@||20', 0),
('TOS', 'Take One', 5, 'A national level short film competition', 'Ragam &#39;13 presents before you South India&#39;s biggest short film competition, <b>Take One</b>.<br/><br/> \r\n\r\nIt&#39;s an open event which will be judged by an expert panel of <br/>\r\n<i>Anjali Menon (Usthad Hotel and Manjadikuru fame)<br/>\r\nRajesh Pillai (Traffic fame)<br/>\r\nBobby-Sanjay (Traffic and Notebook fame)<br/></i><br/><br/>\r\nBest short film will be featured in Asianet Channel.<br/>\r\nWinner gets the chance to work with the next production of &#39;Media Village&#39;.<br/><br/>\r\nWinner of the Best Director title will get a chance to interact with Anjali Menon.<br/> \r\nWinner of the Best Scriptwriter title will get a chance to interact with Bobby-Sanjay.<br/>\r\nStand a chance to win pro-show tickets, Nikon goodies in addition to prizes worth INR 12K. ||sec||Rules and Regulations||ttl||<ul>\r\n<li>TAKE ONE is an open-event. Entries are invited from all.</li>\r\n<li>The entries have to be original. Content copied from any external source shall lead to direct disqualification.</li>\r\n<li>The entry shouldâ€™ve been made within 18 months of the final submission date.</li>\r\n<li>The Registration Fee for the event is INR 300 (Three hundred rupees only) and must be remitted into the HDFC Bank account (Branch- Ramanattukara) with account number <i>15981930000817</i>.</li>\r\n<li>There is no subject/theme for the competition in particular.</li>\r\n<li>The Film cannot exceed a total of 20 minutes running time, not including the title card and credits.</li>\r\n<li>Entries may be in any language, but suitable on-screen English subtitles must be furnished.</li>\r\n<li>Presence of any form of vulgar, obscene, pornographic or religiously offensive content material-thematic or otherwise-will not be tolerated and will lead to direct disqualification.</li>\r\n<li>Only selected entries screened by the jury will be displayed during the festival and the screening will be solely on the discretion of the jury.</li>\r\n<li>Physical presence of the Applicant is not mandatory.</li>\r\n<li>All Films must be submitted to us in a single DVD (DVD-R, DVD+R, DVD-R DL, DVD+R DL), encoded in industry-standard video formats viz. AVI, VOB or MPEG. Entries that are of unrecognized video formats shall not be considered.</li>\r\n<li>The DVD may be sent via speed post along with the following:</li><br/>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Registration form (&lt;a href="/2013/takeoneform.pdf" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none;color:rgb(248,166,119);">Download</a>)</li>\r\n<li>Copy of the receipt received after remitting the Registration fees of INR 300 into our bank account.</li>\r\n<li>Photo-copy of any Photo ID Card of the Director of the entry.</li>\r\n<li>The complete list of the cast and crew of the entry printed in an A4 size sheet.</li>\r\n</ul></li><br/>\r\n<li>Mailing Address :<br/><br/>\r\n<ul>\r\nThe Co-ordinator,<br/>\r\nTake One Short Film Competition<br/>\r\nRagamâ€™13<br/>\r\nNIT Calicut Campus<br/>\r\nNITC P.O, Calicut-673601<br/><br/>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>In order to ensure the safe delivery of your package, the participants are instructed to email the details of the speed post, as soon as they send it, to takeone@ragam.org.in .</li>\r\n<li>The quality of the video should be suitable for screening of the Film using a standard projector.</li>\r\n<li>The entries should be submitted on or before 5 March 2013.</li>\r\n</ul>||sec||Please Note:||ttl||<ul>\r\n<li>No additional weightage will be given for hiring professional help in the technical aspects of the film such as Cinematography, Editing, etc.</li>\r\n<li>It is the sole responsibility of the Applicant to ensure that the submitted DVD plays in its entirety on an industry-standard DVD player prior to submitting it to the Competition. In the event that a submitted disc does not play, the Organizers will attempt, but is under no obligation, to contact the Applicant using the contact information provided on the sub